40|$|Abstract: This paper {{dealt with}} the {{measurement}} and analysis of electromagnetic waves radiated from a partial discharge (PD) source in insulation oil to apply condition monitoring of oil-immersed transformers. Two types of narrow-band <b>monopole</b> <b>antennas</b> with the resonant frequency of a 500 MHz and a 1 GHz were designed and fabricated. Also, a needle-plane electrode system was manufactured to simulate PDs and the curvature radius of the needle is 10 μm and {{the diameter of the}} plane is 60 mm. Electromagnetic wave was measured by the PD measurement system with the <b>monopole</b> <b>antennas.</b> Detection sensitivity of the fabricated antenna was compared for the same PD magnitude; 620 mVpeak for the 500 MHz antenna and 960 mVpeak for the 1 GHz antenna to the PD magnitude of 74 pC. Consequently, the 1 GHz monopol...|$|R
